in greco - roman mythology , arachne ( ; from , cognate with latin araneus)r. s. p. beekes , etymological dictionary of greek , brill , 2009 , p. 124 . was a mortal woman and talented weaver who challenged athena , goddess of wisdom and crafts , and was transformed into a spider .

what a goddess : this greek goddess of war & handicraft changed arachne into a spider after a weaving contest between them

